# Weather Application - Setup and other info
## Packages needed to run this project:
- node
- npm
- sqlite3


## Running the project

### Server
- navigate to the /server folder
- node index.js

### Client
- navigate to /client folder
- npm run dev


## How it works

### The database
    When the server is running, the weather API is polled every 5 minutes. Each reading is saved to the sqlite database (weather.db). When you open the client, the last 24 readings will be shown, and then every time a new data point is polled, it is added live onto the graph


